        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 21 at 8:02PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 802 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Bingham to Mount Hope. Movement was east
at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rainelle, Babcock State Park, Mount Hope, Piney View, Meadow Bridge,
and Thurmond.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 64 in West Virginia between mile markers 134 and 137.
Route 19 between mile markers 5 and 8.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
